Question : You are given a number n.

You must create an ArrayList of size n using the numbers:1, 2, 3, ..., n
Each number must appear exactly once.

This means the array must be a permutation of numbers from 1 to n.

Special Rule (Important)

For any three positions in the array:

i < k < j

The middle number must not be the average of the two outer numbers.

Mathematically, this must NOT happen:

2 × nums[k] = nums[i] + nums[j]

If this condition never happens anywhere in the array, the array is called a Beautiful Array.

Example 1

Input:

n = 4

One possible output:

[2,1,4,3]

Why it works:

No three numbers satisfy:

2 × middle = left + right

So this array is beautiful.

Example 2

Input:

n = 5

One possible output:

[3,1,2,5,4]

This array also satisfies the rule.

Important Notes

The array must contain all numbers from 1 to n.

Each number appears only once.

You can return any valid beautiful array.

There will always be at least one solution.

Constraints
1 ≤ n ≤ 1000
Simple Idea of the Rule

The rule prevents patterns like:

1,2,3

Because:

2 is the average of 1 and 3

So that pattern is not allowed.

But arrays like:

2,1,3

are allowed because the average rule does not happen.
fun main() {
 println("beautiful ArrayList: ${beautifulArrayList(3)}")
}
// Tm : O(n! * n³)
fun beautifulArrayList(n: Int): ArrayList<Int> {

    val nums = (1..n).toCollection(ArrayList())
    val permutations = ArrayList<ArrayList<Int>>()

    fun generate(start: Int) {

        if (start == nums.size) {
            permutations.add(ArrayList(nums))
            return
        }

        for (i in start until nums.size) {

            // swap
            val temp = nums[start]
            nums[start] = nums[i]
            nums[i] = temp

            generate(start + 1)

            // backtrack (swap back)
            nums[i] = nums[start]
            nums[start] = temp
        }
    }

    generate(0)

    for (perm in permutations) {
        if (isBeautiful(perm)) {
            return perm
        }
    }

    return ArrayList()
}
fun isBeautiful(arr: ArrayList<Int>): Boolean {

    val n = arr.size

    for (i in 0 until n) {
        for (j in i + 1 until n) {
            for (k in i + 1 until j) {

                if (2 * arr[k] == arr[i] + arr[j]) {
                    return false
                }

            }
        }
    }

    return true
}
